{"key":"processedPost-8826890","value":{"id":8826890,"first":8822300,"last":8827291,"when":1219714370,"utime":"08/26/08 04:32 AM","content":"Just about any analog hygrometer you get at a cigar shop will work.&nbsp; The biggest problem is they're all made in china and basically all crap.&nbsp; You'll need to buy three, to get two that work.&nbsp; I like to keep two in each greenhouse in order to know when one gets out of calibration.<br /><br />As for drips, you can fill trays with damp perlite, and use those to cover any empty shelf space, and also line them up edge to edge on the floor to catch drips.&nbsp; The perlite will catch the drips and return them to the air as humidity.&nbsp; Having them cover any empty shelf space really goes a long way towards correcting humidity problems in mini-greenhouses.<br />RR","title":"Re: Humidity reading woes","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}